summary:
Results-driven professional with a diverse background in animal husbandry, online marketing, customer service, and a passion for technology. I am currently transitioning my career path into the IT industry through the Masterclass Professional IT traineeship at Calco.

My journey began with a bachelor's degree in Animal Husbandry. Next to my studies, I worked as a tutor in Dutch, English, and Math, honing my communication and teaching skills. I later worked as a Customer Advisor, where I provided great service while resolving customer queries. This role further strengthened my interpersonal skills and reinforced my dedication to helping others.

Driven by my desire for adventure, I have pursued diverse opportunities abroad. What started with living in the United States during my early years, lead to volunteering as a teacher's assistant in Peru and completing an internship at a service and therapy dog training facility in Texas. During these adventures I have developed adaptability, resilience, and a global mindset.

I am grateful for my experience as an online marketing intern at Beaphar. Here, I enhanced the website's search engine optimization (SEO), which included delving into HTML to implement new features. This experience showcased my precision, adaptability, and ability to learn new skills swiftly. It was also a turning point that made me realize I wanted to pursue IT professionally. 

With my transition into IT, I am now eager to apply my analytical thinking, problem-solving abilities, and collaborative nature in a role that will help me grow into a true IT professional.
